</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="1530" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[178,1085,378,458]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1530">
Etymology: The generic epithet is a Greek compound name derived from 
<emphasis box="[1033,1085,379,400]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1530">aspis</emphasis>
(= shield) and 
<emphasis box="[326,381,408,429]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1530">tonus</emphasis>
(= stretching). I refer to the pronotal lateral expansion resulting from a well-developed tubercle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
